#!N  #!Rpanzoom Panning and Zooming into and out of the Image 
#!N #!EC #!N #!N You can zoom into or out of 
the image and change the look-to point at the same time, 
using the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Pan/Zoom #!EF mode. In this mode, the left 
and right mouse buttons work the same as they do in 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Zoom #!EF mode, except that the point on the image 
where you initially click becomes the new look-to point, and therefore 
the center of your zoom action. As you move the mouse 
pointer away from the point where you initially clicked, the rectangle 
enlarges. As you move the mouse pointer towards the point where 
you initially clicked, the rectangle shrinks. For information about the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
Zoom #!EF mode, see  #!Lzooming,dxall306 h Zooming into and out of the Image  #!EL  . #!N #!N To select  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
Pan/Zoom #!EF mode, select its option from the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Mode #!EF 
option box, or use the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Ctrl+G #!EF accelerator key. Note: 
You can also enable  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Pan/Zoom #!EF mode by using the 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   intrctnMode #!EF parameter to the Image tool (see Image in 
IBM Visualization Data Explorer User's Reference). #!N #!N #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   Next 
Topic #!EF #!N #!N  #!Lnavigat,dxall309 h Navigating in a Scene  #!EL  #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   #!N 
